      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 🎬 AUTO MOVIE DIRECTOR\n\n## 1 — WRITE. Type your movie idea in the big box on the Movie Planner. Pick how many scenes and how many seconds each scene runs.\n\n## 2 — STORYBOARD. On the Movie Renderer, set the mode switch to \"1) storyboard\" and press Queue. In a few minutes you get one picture per scene, laid out like a comic page.\n\n## 3 — APPROVE. Like it? Touch nothing. Want changes? Edit your idea (or type into any scene's own box) and Queue again.\n\n## 4 — MOVIE. Flip the mode switch to \"2) storyboard to movie\" and press Queue. Every scene comes back with motion and sound, joined into one finished MP4 that plays right on the node.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
